    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Colonel General Aleksandr Lapin is the former Chief of Staff of the Russian Ground Forces. In this capacity, he was the Commander-in-Chief of the Russian ground troops directly participating in Russia’s war of aggression against Ukraine. He was previously the Commander of the Central Military District of the Russian Federation, including during Russia’s war against Ukraine. As such, he commanded the Russian 2022 offensive in the Chernihiv and Sumy directions.",
